India Defeats Bangladesh by 87 Runs in Opening Game of Cricket World Cup

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-02-19T16:43:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-19/india-defeats-bangladesh-by-87-runs-in-opening-game-of-cricket-world-cup.html
Virender Sehwag scored 175 to lead  India  to an 87-run victory over Bangladesh in the opening game
of the Cricket World Cup.  Virat Kohli scored 100 not out for India, which reached
370-4 in its 50 overs after losing the toss and batting first in
the matchup of two of the tournament’s host nations.  Munaf Patel then took 4-48 as India limited Bangladesh to
283-9 in its innings. Tamin Iqbal scored 70 to lead Bangladesh,
while Shakib Al Hasan had 55.  Kenya meets New Zealand and  Sri Lanka , the third hosting
country, plays Canada in tomorrow’s games.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  